        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(auth): resolve custom provider secretref-managed apiKey from runtime snapshot",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nCustom providers with `apiKey: secretref-managed` (resolved via SecretRef) fail with 503 `auth_unavailable` after update to 2026.6.5. The auth resolution chain correctly blocks on the managed-secretref marker, but the fallback path that reads the resolved apiKey from the runtime config snapshot was never reached for custom providers without a matching plugin hook.\n\n`resolveProviderSyntheticRuntimeAuth` only looked at plugin-returned auth; when no plugin hook matched the custom provider, it returned `{}` instead of falling back to the resolved apiKey stored in the runtime snapshot.\n\nFixes #92097.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/agents/model-auth.ts`: `resolveProviderSyntheticRuntimeAuth` now falls back to reading `providerConfig?.apiKey` directly from the config when plugin hooks return nothing, and also checks the runtime config snapshot when direct config auth is missing.\n- `src/agents/model-auth.test.ts`: Added regression test verifying a custom provider with `NON_ENV_SECRETREF_MARKER` source config correctly resolves the runtime snapshot apiKey.\n- `scripts/repro/issue-92097-secretref-custom-provider.mts`: Standalone reproduction script.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: Custom provider with `secretref-managed` apiKey now resolves the actual key from the runtime config snapshot instead of failing with auth_unavailable.\n- **Real environment tested**: Linux 4.19.112-2.el8.x86_64, Node.js v22.19.0, local source checkout at `main`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n  - `npx tsx scripts/repro/issue-92097-secretref-custom-provider.mts`\n  - `pnpm test src/agents/model-auth.test.ts --run`\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n\n```text\n=== Reproduction for issue #92097 ===\nSource config apiKey: secretref-managed\nRuntime config apiKey: resolved-secretref-key\n\nResolved auth: {\n  apiKey: 'resolved-secretref-key',\n  source: 'models.providers.cliproxyapi',\n  mode: 'api-key'\n}\n\nPASS: Custom provider secretref-managed apiKey correctly resolved from runtime snapshot.\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: The resolved auth object contains the real `apiKey` from the runtime snapshot, with correct `source` and `mode` fields.\n- **What was not tested**: Actual SecretRef resolution lifecycle (runtime snapshot is injected directly in the repro); other auth modes (OAuth, profile-based) for custom providers.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test src/agents/model-auth.test.ts --run` — 59 passed (including new regression test)\n- `pnpm build` — passed\n- `npx oxlint --import-plugin --config .oxlintrc.json src/agents/model-auth.ts src/agents/model-auth.test.ts` — passed\n- `pnpm format:fix src/agents/model-auth.ts src/agents/model-auth.test.ts` — no changes needed",
        "branch": "fix/92097-secretref-custom-provider-auth",
